         <abstract>
            <p>Consider the approximation of the solution $u$ of an elliptic boundary value problem by means of a finite element Galerkin method of order $r$, so that the approximate solution $u_h$ satisfies $u_h - u = O(h^r)$. Bramble and Schatz (Math. Comp., v. 31, 1977, pp. 94-111) have constructed, for elements satisfying certain uniformity conditions, a simple function $K_h$ such that $K_h \ast u_h - u = O(h^{2r-2})$ in the interior. Their result is generalized here to obtain similar superconvergent order interior approximations also for derivatives of $u$.</p>
          </abstract>
